description: This file defines a Data class for managing data associated with DOM elements or objects, including methods for setting, getting, removing, and checking data. It is part of the jQuery library's internal data management system.

classes.name: Data
classes.description: A class for managing internal data storage for DOM elements or objects.

methods.name: key
methods.description: Generates or retrieves a unique key for the owner object to associate data.

methods.name: set
methods.description: Sets data for a given owner object, either by key-value pair or by object.

methods.name: get
methods.description: Retrieves data associated with an owner object by key.

methods.name: access
methods.description: Gets or sets data depending on provided arguments.

methods.name: remove
methods.description: Removes data associated with an owner object for specified keys.

methods.name: hasData
methods.description: Checks if an owner object has any associated data.

methods.name: discard
methods.description: Deletes all data associated with an owner object.
